  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nAndroid screen flickers while navigating\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17097240/211683411-de884c4a-2b71-42da-a54c-786bb1b0e9ec.mp4\r\n\r\n### Cause\r\nLayout animations are disabled by default in current version (2.3.3), and on [enabling](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/9ed89ac97dc5a37dfabf1c8a232d45cf730fcdd0/src/react_native/reanimated.cljs#L20) them this flicker happens ([reference](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/13452#issuecomment-1159800179)).\r\nAnd even if we don't enable them by default, and we use any layout animation from reanimated then they [will be enabled](https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/pull/2651#issue-1059867386) at runtime. This enabling of layout animation at runtime also breaks layout, as mentioned in [comment](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/14618#issuecomment-1371071337).\r\n\r\nSo, for fixing this issue either we can try to upgrade reanimated\r\n(not sure if that will fix it, but still upgrade has its own [problems](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/13452#issuecomment-1159800641)),\r\nor for now we can avoid using layout animations. cc @yqrashawn\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open community chat\r\n2) Restart app\r\n3) Press back button in community chat\r\n(@status-im/mobile-qa Please can you verify issue. Compare current nightly with version before https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/14618 for verification)\r\n",
